// InventoryReport carries a node's software inventory for affectedness matching.
// It rides its OWN control-stream arm, never the metrics path: the metrics sink is
// capped and uncompressed, while an SBOM is large and cold-path. content_hash is
// the agent's SHA-256 over the UNCOMPRESSED canonical CycloneDX document for the
// node's WHOLE current component set — the same value the heartbeat carries, so the
// controller only ingests when the hash it holds differs (or it holds none). The
// controller binds the report to the authenticated (workspace, node) of the stream;
// the node_id here is advisory. format is the SBOM media type
// ("application/vnd.cyclonedx+json").
//
// A report is either FULL or a DELTA:
//   - full: full=true and sbom carries the whole zstd CycloneDX document. The first
//     report after enroll is always full, and a delta whose base the controller cannot
//     match falls back to a full on the next cycle.
//   - delta: full=false and base_hash names the content_hash the delta applies on
//     top of (the agent's last controller-held set). added/removed carry only the
//     components that changed since that base. The controller applies them to the set
//     it holds under base_hash and checks the result hashes to content_hash; if it
//     holds a different base it rejects the delta and asks for a full (see
//     InventoryControl). sbom is empty on a delta.
